    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/fea-compression-bending-claim-001",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "FEA accurately predicts non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending QoIs within acceptance bounds",
      "description": "The FEA modeling framework (FDA-validated Ansys implementation, DePuy Synthes material library v3.2) predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading. All three quantities of interest fall within the pre-specified acceptance bounds: relative difference <10% and E/uval <1.96 for each QoI. The claim is supported by multi-laboratory experimental correlation (N=11) and ensemble model agreement across three independent FEA implementations.",
      "scope": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct; ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol; titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V ELI; polyaxial screw-rod interface; two independent test laboratories.",
      "purpose": "Establish that FEA simulation results are credible for regulatory submission in lieu of additional physical prototypes, thereby supporting the design validation strategy for the non-cannulated variant."
    },
